    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="43"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bryan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis, Brazil</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 252.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm your cipher
                        telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d43fn1">Printed, ante.</note> of this date, and
                    to refer to my No. 249 of to-day. I am glad to receive instructions which
                    justify me in further protesting against this obnoxious law prohibiting
                    trade-marks in Portuguese, to which I made objection both yesterday and
                    previously at the foreign office.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Page Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
